## Section 6: 8259 coherent-poll stub as insurance (Increment 4)

Open question the closed gate does NOT answer: does the SRM
device-interrupt handler resolve the source via the 8259
(OCW3 poll at 0x20 / 0xA0, INTA, or ELCR at 0x4D0-0x4D1) or off DIRn
with a DRIR-keyed dispatch table? Now that b_irq<1> can assert, this
is directly observable.

Recommendation: do NOT gate Increment 2 on the answer. Stub the 8259
with a coherent OCW3-poll register that returns IRQ4 when DRIR<55> is
asserted, so the handler resolves correctly whether or not it polls.
Then, after the post-assert trace:
- handler touches 0x20/0xA0/0x4D0: PROMOTE the stub to the minimal
  surface the handler actually reads.
- handler dispatches off DIRn only: DELETE the stub.
This is cheap insurance against the failure mode where the handler
polls, gets a spurious read, and dispatches IRQ7-spurious instead of
the COM1 ISR.

