## Section 7: Data fidelity flags

- DRIR<55> is BOARD wiring, not 21272 HRM. The 21272 HRM defines
  DRIR<55:0> as 56 generic device lines; which bit the ISA/SIO bridge
  output lands on is in the board/system manual. Mark the constant
  _PROVISIONAL and verify against the board manual before it becomes a
  C2 device-interrupt decode match. A wrong bit is silent dropped
  interrupts. [COWORK: cite the board manual section once verified.]
- UART IER vs CPU HW_IER: distinct registers, distinct names in code
  (Section 4). EIEN<1> = bit 34, EI level 23, per 2026-05-19 Phase D.

